Luca_PI wrote:

>project: SharpNEAT
>file: form1.cs
>procedure: InititialisePopulationFromSeedPopulation()
>
>if(seedPopulation.IsCompatibleWithNetwork
>(selectedExperiment.NetworkEvaluator.InputNeuronCount,
>	selectedExperiment.NetworkEvaluator.OutputNeuronCount))
>
>instead of:
>
>if(!seedPopulation.IsCompatibleWithNetwork
>(selectedExperiment.NetworkEvaluator.InputNeuronCount,
>	selectedExperiment.NetworkEvaluator.OutputNeuronCount))
>
>

Hi Luca,

Thanks for the feedback, I have looked into this and at first glance it 
seems OK. Is there a particular population file that is failing to load? 
If so check that all of the genomes in the population have the correct 
number of input and output nodes for the problem domain you have 
selected. If there is still a problem then feel free to email me the 
population file and I'll have a deeper look.

Colin.
